13/04/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- OSCE Ambassador to Tirana Pavel Vacek urged the country's political parties Wednesday (12 April) to immediately resume dialogue on crucial electoral reform and ensure that a related parliamentary committee starts work. Praising the recent reconciliation agreement between the ruling and opposition parties that ended a two-month parliamentary crisis, Vacek stressed that no more time must be wasted ahead of elections this autumn.
In other news Wednesday, the Council of Europe announced that its rapporteurs had wrapped up a mission to Tirana. Information they gathered will be used to prepare a new monitoring report, due for official release in November. (Albanian News - 13/04/06; CoE Web site - 12/04/06)
